text.tspan: Global airline passenger capacity and traffic
Available kilometers is a measure of passenger carrying capacity: it is the number of seats available multiplied by the number of kilometers
flown. Passenger seat kilometers measures the actual number of kilometers flown by paying customers.
Data source: International Civil Aviation Organization via Airlines for America (2023)
